{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-92b6f3194c3cbb15", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# Qwen3-ASR Technical Report\narXiv: 2601.21337\nAuthors: Xian Shi, Xiong Wang, Zhifang Guo, Yongqi Wang, Pei Zhang, Xinyu Zhang, Zishan Guo, Hongkun Hao, Yu Xi, Baosong Yang, Jin Xu, Jingren Zhou, Junyang Lin\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: asr\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduces the Qwen3-ASR family, featuring two all-in-one ASR models that achieve state-of-the-art multilingual and dialectal speech recognition while remaining competitive with top proprietary APIs.\n  2. Presents Qwen3-ForcedAligner-0.6B, the first LLM-based non-autoregressive forced aligner that provides highly accurate multilingual timestamps at flexible granularities.\n  3. Demonstrates exceptional inference efficiency, with the Qwen3-ASR-0.6B model achieving an optimal accuracy-efficiency trade-off and processing up to 2,000 seconds of audio per second at high concurrency.\n  4. Releases all model weights under the Apache 2.0 license alongside a comprehensive, open-source inference and fine-tuning framework to accelerate speech recognition research.\n\nTags: ASR, ASR/隐式对齐-AED, ASR/训练-监督\n===\nPaper 2505.18644 not found", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "8072e7a1-10b2-4807-b38a-8c763f8d9c2c", "uuid": "9b5bd54f-29cf-4a83-8b2f-402f5e7d1f7a", "timestamp": "2026-07-06T10:30:48.040Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# Qwen3-ASR Technical Report\narXiv: 2601.21337\nAuthors: Xian Shi, Xiong Wang, Zhifang Guo, Yongqi Wang, Pei Zhang, Xinyu Zhang, Zishan Guo, Hongkun Hao, Yu Xi, Baosong Yang, Jin Xu, Jingren Zhou, Junyang Lin\nYear: 2026 | Venue: \nTopic: asr\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduces the Qwen3-ASR family, featuring two all-in-one ASR models that achieve state-of-the-art multilingual and dialectal speech recognition while remaining competitive with top proprietary APIs.\n  2. Presents Qwen3-ForcedAligner-0.6B, the first LLM-based non-autoregressive forced aligner that provides highly accurate multilingual timestamps at flexible granularities.\n  3. Demonstrates exceptional inference efficiency, with the Qwen3-ASR-0.6B model achieving an optimal accuracy-efficiency trade-off and processing up to 2,000 seconds of audio per second at high concurrency.\n  4. Releases all model weights under the Apache 2.0 license alongside a comprehensive, open-source inference and fine-tuning framework to accelerate speech recognition research.\n\nTags: ASR, ASR/隐式对齐-AED, ASR/训练-监督\n===\nPaper 2505.18644 not found", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
